This paper deals with distributed algorithms in networks, specifically in the context of population protocols. The problem being addressed is multi-choice majority voting, which is a common problem in distributed computing. The paper proposes a new model called "Broadcasting Population Protocol" and designs two algorithms for solving the problem. The paper also analyzes the time and message complexities of the algorithms. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems).
